Well, both of us were wrong.
- What else?

34
00:02:38,860 --> 00:02:40,820
Can't he be wrong once?

35
00:02:40,820 --> 00:02:43,759
But he is Su Yu.

36
00:03:10,948 --> 00:03:12,770
Mrs. Jin.

37
00:03:12,770 --> 00:03:16,040
This child is getting more handsome.

38
00:03:28,279 --> 00:03:33,380
Have you heard this child's mother got married again?

39
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:34,980
What's so strange about getting married?

40
00:03:34,980 --> 00:03:37,740
The couple has been divorced
for more than ten years.

41
00:03:37,740 --> 00:03:41,620
But this time, she married a rich man.

42
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:43,140
Rich man?

43
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:45,060
How rich is he?

44
00:03:45,060 --> 00:03:47,000
How rich?

45
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:50,839
A big villa. Several cars.

46
00:03:50,839 --> 00:03:53,279
And several companies.

47
00:03:53,279 --> 00:03:55,479
So rich?

48
00:03:55,479 --> 00:03:59,000
Well, then he is old, right?

49
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:03,799
Same age as Su Yu's mother.

50
00:04:05,559 --> 00:04:07,160
Second marriage?

51
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:09,220
That's for sure.

52
00:04:09,220 --> 00:04:13,060
I heard he also has a boy.

53
00:04:13,060 --> 00:04:14,600
Look at her. Look at her.

54
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:16,240
Leaving her own son behind

55
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:19,219
to be a stepmother for the other.

56
00:04:19,219 --> 00:04:21,288
Alas.

57
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:27,000
Dad, I'm back.

58
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,160
You're home, Son.

59
00:04:36,072 --> 00:04:37,559
What's this?

60
00:04:37,559 --> 00:04:39,908
Ten catties of potatoes.

61
00:04:39,908 --> 00:04:41,120
Why did you buy so many?

62
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:44,260
I didn't buy them. I got them at the street corner.

63
00:04:44,260 --> 00:04:48,060
As long as you go to listen to the class, you can get a box of potatoes for free.

64
00:04:50,059 --> 00:04:53,940
Tell me, how much money did you get scammed out of?

65
00:04:53,940 --> 00:04:56,099
Can you stop hanging out
with a bunch of old men?

66
00:04:56,099 --> 00:04:58,060
How old are you?

67
00:04:58,060 --> 00:05:00,520
And how many times have I told you?

68
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:03,120
Those free giveaways are scams.

69
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:05,660
Their goal is to brainwash you, and you will buy
a bunch of useless health care products.

70
00:05:05,660 --> 00:05:07,540
It is not health care products.

71
00:05:07,540 --> 00:05:10,640
It is plasters, specifically for treating my waist injury.

72
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:12,940
And it's only 9.9 yuan for ten patches.

73
00:05:12,940 --> 00:05:14,899
Where can you find such a steal?

74
00:05:14,899 --> 00:05:16,340
Even if the plasters don't work,

75
00:05:16,340 --> 00:05:19,560
9.9 for ten catties of potatoes
is worth it, right?

76
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:21,559
Son, don't you love potatoes?

77
00:05:21,559 --> 00:05:23,160
Go and bake some.

78
00:05:38,399 --> 00:05:41,240
These are your ten catties of potatoes?
- What's wrong?

79
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:43,720
This is nine catties of dirt
and one catty of vegetables.

80
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:46,480
Let me have a check.

81
00:05:51,799 --> 00:05:54,060
What a scam!

82
00:05:56,880 --> 00:05:58,880
But it's not wrong.

83
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:00,740
Potatoes, potatoes.

84
00:06:00,740 --> 00:06:03,040
Which are vegetables growing in dirt, right?

85
00:06:05,096 --> 00:06:09,084
Dad. Did you apply the plaster?

86
00:06:23,639 --> 00:06:26,640
Sir, Madam, the dishes are all ready.

87
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:30,580
Auntie, let me help him peel them.

88
00:06:30,580 --> 00:06:32,739
You could go take a break.

89
00:06:41,399 --> 00:06:44,600
Wu Bi. Dinner time.

90
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:25,460
Wu Bi, I heard you love king crab. So, I went to the fish market--

91
00:07:25,460 --> 00:07:28,959
Please watch your words.

92
00:07:28,959 --> 00:07:31,000
I have my own mother.

93
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,239
She passed away.

94
00:07:33,239 --> 00:07:37,740
If you died too, I'd call you mom.

95
00:07:37,740 --> 00:07:41,079
You jerk, how can you talk like that?

96
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:44,300
Zhenghao, don't be angry.

97
00:07:44,300 --> 00:07:48,839
As it's our first meeting, it's normal to be a bit estranged.

98
00:07:53,799 --> 00:07:55,140
Don't peel it for him.

99
00:07:55,140 --> 00:07:56,879
Let him do it himself.

100
00:07:56,879 --> 00:08:00,519
Alright, kids at this age are rebellious.

101
00:08:00,519 --> 00:08:03,720
My son is even more stubborn.

102
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:09,120
I heard your son is also a sophomore, right?

103
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:10,048
Yes.

104
00:08:10,048 --> 00:08:12,036
Which school is he attending?

105
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:15,880
What high school is it?

106
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:17,680
I can't remember at the moment.

107
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:20,440
Anyway, an ordinary one near his home.

108
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:23,760
With the normal teaching environment.

109
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:27,299
But my child can always rank first
in the whole school.

110
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:32,580
Such a good talent, we can't let him go to waste.

111
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:36,459
What about transferring him to Wu Bi's school?

112
00:08:36,459 --> 00:08:39,499
Private schools are generally better.

113
00:08:39,499 --> 00:08:42,359
And the two kids can keep each other company.

114
00:08:45,799 --> 00:08:49,440
Really? I heard that school
is hard to get into.

115
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:53,860
Wu Bi, are you done eating?

116
00:08:53,860 --> 00:08:55,579
I'm full.

117
00:09:50,379 --> 00:09:54,400
Mom, this boy is dressed so shabbily.

118
00:09:55,239 --> 00:09:56,559
Don't talk nonsense.

119
00:09:56,559 --> 00:10:00,259
Don't discriminate against kids
who are worse off than you.

120
00:10:00,259 --> 00:10:03,960
Mom, are you carving this to give away?

121
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:09,119
Yes. A friend of mine's son
has a birthday next month.

122
00:10:09,119 --> 00:10:13,780
She asked me to make a statue as a birthday gift for her son.

123
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:16,120
Is it Aunt Zhang?

124
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:19,080
Is it Aunt Liang?

125
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:20,300
No.

126
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:23,039
She is a new friend of mine.

127
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:31,020
He has a mole on his ear.

128
00:10:31,020 --> 00:10:32,280
Yeah.

129
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:35,320
Kids with moles on their ears are smart.

130
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:40,100
Mom, when do you plan to give it to her?

131
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:45,119
In a couple of days,I'll send it over when I am free.

132
00:10:45,919 --> 00:10:49,220
Come on. I'll teach you how to draw.

133
00:10:50,159 --> 00:10:52,239
Yeah.

134
00:10:52,239 --> 00:10:53,580
Great job.

135
00:10:53,580 --> 00:10:59,280
Mom, today my dad brought that woman home.

136
00:11:01,239 --> 00:11:03,180
They got married.

137
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:27,208
Mom,I miss you so much.

138
00:11:27,772 --> 00:11:34,092
(Endless Stories)

139
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:43,059
It didn't work, Son.

140
00:11:43,059 --> 00:11:45,359
Let's go to another place and try it.

141
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:09,960
Son, stop pulling.

142
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:12,080
It hurts too much.

143
00:12:21,924 --> 00:12:23,480
Wu Bi.

144
00:12:24,760 --> 00:12:27,299
What's wrong?
Do you have time to date me today?

145
00:12:28,119 --> 00:12:30,579
Auntie, please do me a favor.

146
00:12:30,579 --> 00:12:34,100
No favors between us.
Just tell me if you need anything.

147
00:12:34,100 --> 00:12:36,392
I want to transfer.

148
00:12:36,392 --> 00:12:40,212
Transfer? Why do you want to transfer?

149
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:46,619
My dad wants to transfer

150
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:50,720
his mistress's son to our school.

151
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:52,216
I don't want to see him.

152
00:12:52,216 --> 00:12:55,648
(Beijing Riyue Weiming Senior High School)

153
00:12:56,479 --> 00:12:57,680
What are you guys doing?

154
00:12:57,680 --> 00:12:59,860
Why are you leaving? Play for a while.

155
00:12:59,860 --> 00:13:02,112
Stop it. I'm telling you.

156
00:13:02,112 --> 00:13:03,359
Stop it.

157
00:13:03,359 --> 00:13:05,348
Why are you getting anxious now?

158
00:13:05,348 --> 00:13:06,620
What's the matter? What's the matter?

159
00:13:06,620 --> 00:13:08,956
Can't take the heat?  - Go, go, go.

160
00:13:08,956 --> 00:13:10,712
Su Yu,

161
00:13:12,520 --> 00:13:16,500
let me introduce a friend to you. My deskmate. He's Mao Chong.

162
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:19,000
Machine? What machine?

163
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:21,280
Mao Chong. Him!

164
00:13:21,280 --> 00:13:25,000
Him? So what about the machine?

165
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:27,000
I am Mao Chong, not machine.

166
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:29,060
Bro, are you a little stupid?

167
00:13:29,060 --> 00:13:32,380
My name is Mao Chong. Mao Chong is my name.

168
00:13:32,380 --> 00:13:34,400
You're silly instead.
Your parents are silly instead.

169
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:36,220
What a crappy name they gave you.

170
00:13:36,220 --> 00:13:38,759
May I ask for your honorable name, sir?

171
00:13:38,759 --> 00:13:41,640
My last name is Han
and my first name is Bokuang.

172
00:13:43,719 --> 00:13:46,000
Han Bokuang.

173
00:13:47,119 --> 00:13:50,780
Your parents' action was pretty wild too.

174
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:53,459
Let's go.

175
00:13:53,459 --> 00:13:54,768
Go.

176
00:13:59,920 --> 00:14:01,960
Quite delicious, huh?

177
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:04,264
Whose car is this?

178
00:14:04,264 --> 00:14:06,188
Mercedes. Mercedes.

179
00:14:06,188 --> 00:14:07,890
BMW, BMW.

180
00:14:07,890 --> 00:14:09,520
Son!

181
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:12,359
Son, I have some great news to tell you.

182
00:14:12,359 --> 00:14:14,440
Get in the car with Mom.

183
00:14:15,760 --> 00:14:18,320
Please mind your words, madam.

184
00:14:22,679 --> 00:14:25,900
I only have a dad, no mom.

185
00:14:32,799 --> 00:14:34,900
If it weren't for your dad,

186
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:37,579
I wouldn't have left you back then.

187
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:41,088
What did he do wrong?

188
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:44,479
Children don't understand adult matters.

189
00:14:44,479 --> 00:14:46,459
He's just stubborn.

190
00:14:46,459 --> 00:14:49,700
He spent all day in that small factory. He would do nothing else but work.

191
00:14:49,700 --> 00:14:52,440
I'm not like him in personality.
- He's poor.

192
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:54,860
It's not like what you thought.

193
00:14:54,860 --> 00:14:57,459
Alright, let's not talk about this today.

194
00:14:57,459 --> 00:15:01,080
Get in the car with Mom first. Let's talk about something else.

195
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:04,000
If you don't get in the car with me,
I'll go home with you.

196
00:15:11,919 --> 00:15:14,000
That brat.

197
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:17,140
Left with his mom.
- Heartless. Really heartless.

198
00:15:24,039 --> 00:15:25,980
Just say what you have to say.

199
00:15:27,359 --> 00:15:28,980
Eat something first.

200
00:15:28,980 --> 00:15:31,540
It is the best Western restaurant in Beijing.

201
00:15:38,119 --> 00:15:39,559
Potatoes are just a side dish.

202
00:15:39,559 --> 00:15:41,540
Why eat it?

203
00:15:46,799 --> 00:15:49,060
Don't you know how to use a knife and fork?

204
00:15:49,060 --> 00:15:51,100
I will help you cut.

205
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:53,939
If you don't say anything, I'll go back.

206
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:58,440
Alright, alright, I'll listen to my son.

207
00:15:59,280 --> 00:16:01,000
Let's talk about the main issue.

208
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,848
Your stepfather,

209
00:16:05,344 --> 00:16:06,919
which is my husband,

210
00:16:06,919 --> 00:16:09,240
said he wants to transfer you
to an international school.

211
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:11,160
Can you not always interfere with my life?

212
00:16:11,160 --> 00:16:13,080
What do you mean
by interfering with your life?

213
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:14,620
Mom is doing this for your good.

214
00:16:14,620 --> 00:16:17,880
My husband's son is about your age. He's studying there too.

215
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:20,879
What's worse about you? Why can he--
- Enough!

216
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:26,579
There's no way
I'll have any interaction with him.

217
00:16:45,704 --> 00:16:47,060
Su Yu.

218
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:50,379
Give me some reaction, alright?

219
00:16:51,679 --> 00:16:55,779
Wait, why do you have a long face?

220
00:16:55,779 --> 00:16:57,860
Do I?

221
00:16:57,860 --> 00:16:59,500
Haven't I always been like this?

222
00:16:59,500 --> 00:17:04,100
That's true. I haven't seen you smile a few times
since you were little.

223
00:17:04,100 --> 00:17:06,460
If I had such a handsome face like you,

224
00:17:06,460 --> 00:17:09,319
I would rearrange my facial features several times a day.

225
00:17:09,319 --> 00:17:12,460
But you always have a poker face instead.

226
00:17:16,139 --> 00:17:19,460
Fine. I won't say anything. Is that okay?

227
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:29,980
You can't get past me.

228
00:17:29,980 --> 00:17:31,300
Go.

229
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:34,092
Like this.
- I'll hit you.

230
00:17:34,640 --> 00:17:35,800
You can't catch up. Go, go.

231
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,900
- Come back.
- Let's go.

232
00:17:37,900 --> 00:17:39,140
You hit.

233
00:17:39,140 --> 00:17:40,560
Hit me, hit.

234
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:41,760
You hit.

235
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:42,880
You failed.

236
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:45,359
Don't run. Come back.

237
00:17:47,459 --> 00:17:49,000
Harder.

238
00:17:51,199 --> 00:17:54,000
I heard a new student
transferred to our class.

239
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:56,119
So what?

240
00:17:56,119 --> 00:17:58,980
Aren't you curious about
what kind of person he is?

241
00:17:58,980 --> 00:18:01,180
What's there to be curious about?

242
00:18:01,180 --> 00:18:03,319
Alright, you killed the conversation.

243
00:18:03,319 --> 00:18:07,700
With your face, if only you had a little expression,

244
00:18:07,700 --> 00:18:11,479
the title of school hunk
wouldn't have been mine.

245
00:18:34,160 --> 00:18:38,620
Classmates, today, we have a new student in our class.

246
00:18:38,620 --> 00:18:40,384
Please come in.

247
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:47,099
He's quite hot.

248
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:17,976
Let's welcome him.

249
00:19:18,599 --> 00:19:20,180
Oh, my.

250
00:19:20,180 --> 00:19:24,019
The school hunk
is probably going to change hands.

251
00:19:26,560 --> 00:19:28,460
Please introduce yourself.

252
00:19:28,460 --> 00:19:30,340
My name is Wu Bi.

253
00:19:31,119 --> 00:19:32,160
Well, finished?

254
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:34,240
- That's it?
- Finished?

255
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:36,319
He's so dope.

256
00:19:47,308 --> 00:19:50,719
Classmates, what does Zhu Zhiwu's art of persuasion

257
00:19:50,719 --> 00:19:53,940
mean to us modern people?

258
00:19:53,940 --> 00:19:56,780
When you talk,
you shall understand others' feelings.

259
00:19:56,780 --> 00:19:58,499
Not too straightforward.

260
00:19:58,499 --> 00:20:01,060
So that effective communication
can take place.

261
00:20:01,060 --> 00:20:06,140
Also, be good at listening
to other people's opinions and improve yourself.

262
00:20:06,140 --> 00:20:08,959
Only then can you improve your cultivation.

263
00:20:10,560 --> 00:20:13,260
I see you're all sleepy. How about this?

264
00:20:13,260 --> 00:20:17,132
Any volunteer sings a song
