00:24:42,144 --> 00:24:46,332
Qu Yuan whose given name is Ping
and who styled himself as Yuan.

303
00:24:46,332 --> 00:24:52,280
He was a famous poet and politician in the State of Chu
during the Warring States period.

304
00:24:52,280 --> 00:24:56,480
Once served as the minister and official
in the State of Chu.

305
00:24:57,040 --> 00:25:01,180
The Songs of Chu is a collection of poems
by a group of poets led by Qu Yuan

306
00:25:01,180 --> 00:25:05,400
in the State of Chu
during the Warring States period.

307
00:25:06,119 --> 00:25:09,200
Sleeping all day.
Is this how a class president acts?

308
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:12,719
These poems have a common feature.

309
00:25:12,719 --> 00:25:19,380
They used the form, dialect, and rhyme of Chu poetry

310
00:25:19,380 --> 00:25:22,119
to describe the local customs of Chu.

311
00:25:24,839 --> 00:25:30,139
Qu Yuan was trusted by King Huai of Chu in his early years,

312
00:25:30,139 --> 00:25:33,300
handling domestic and foreign affairs.

313
00:25:33,300 --> 00:25:35,400
He advocated good governance.

314
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:39,800
He argued for promoting talents
and improving laws internally,

315
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:44,119
forming an alliance with the State of Qi
to resist the State of Qin externally.

316
00:25:44,119 --> 00:25:46,359
Due to the exclusion
and slander of the nobles,

317
00:25:46,359 --> 00:25:51,179
he was successively exiled
to the Hanbei and Yuanxiang regions.

318
00:25:51,179 --> 00:25:54,300
After the capital of Chu, Ying,
was occupied by the Qin army,

319
00:25:54,300 --> 00:25:56,199
Qu Yuan drowned himself in the Miluo River.

